item.title: Compile error! help?!?
item.dc:creator: @TeleNubby TeleNubby
item.description:
@TeleNubby wrote:

Graham:

Put the whole doc on. That code is fine.

No. You guys, c’mon. This is easy and you should know it.

It means the last bracket was read, and everything was complete. But then outta nowhere another ‘statement’ comes up, and it cannot read it because it does not know where to place it. Look at the code you pasted earlier:

if (c.specialAmount >= 100 && c.specOn == true) {
c.sendFrame126("@yel@S P E C I A L  A T T A C K", 7511);
c.fsBar(500, 0, 7501);
c.fsBar(500, 0, 7502);
c.fsBar(500, 0, 7503);
c.fsBar(500, 0, 7504);
c.fsBar(500, 0, 7505);
c.fsBar(500, 0, 7506);
c.fsBar(500, 0, 7507);
c.fsBar(500, 0, 7508);
c.fsBar(500, 0, 7509);
c.fsBar(500, 0, 7510);
}
}

You have one opening bracket ‘{’. And yes, ‘{’ and ‘}’ are brackets. That one opening bracket should be followed by ONLY ONE closing bracket ‘}’. But look at your code. There are two closing brackets. Just remove that last one, and you’ll be fine.
